data.description: Welcome home to 8902 Camfield Drive, a stunning contemporary home in Alexandria’s coveted Fort Hunt neighborhood. This residence sits on a large, private, quarter-acre lot and features professional landscaping, mature, flowering trees, and a fully fenced, flat backyard.  Upon entering the home, you’re greeted by soaring ceilings, hardwood floors, and a large living room with exposed beams, a gas fireplace, and a wall of windows to let natural light in. A separate dining room is located off of the living room and leads into the renovated galley kitchen, complete with marble counters, a hand-crafted backsplash, soft close cabinetry, a custom pantry, new large-format tile floors, and GE Profile appliances. The main level also features a conveniently located half bath and an expansive playroom/sun room with a built-in banquette, built-in shelves and storage, exposed beams, and French doors leading to the home’s deck and backyard.  Upstairs you’ll find three of the home’s bedrooms, including the primary suite with a beautifully renovated en-suite bathroom. A full bathroom off the hallway and a large linen closet round out this level.  The lower level features a cozy family room with brand-new carpeting and a cast iron electric stove, a space made for movie nights. Just beyond is the home’s fourth bedroom (perfect for guests or a home office), a second, recently renovated half bathroom, and utility space with a full-size washer and dryer, storage space, and additional access to the back yard. The home also features more than 600 square feet of unfinished basement space perfect for all your storage needs or a great spot for your home gym.   The home is perfectly situated for recreational activities. It’s close to Fort Hunt Park, the Potomac River, and George Washington’s Mount Vernon Estate and only three blocks from the GW Parkway bike path/walking trail. In addition, the new owners have a first right of refusal for a Stratford Recreation Association membership (pool and tennis courts; summer parties; swim, tennis, and dive teams for children).   The home is located just 10 miles to Ronald Reagan National Airport, and convenient to Fort Belvoir, the George Washington Memorial Parkway, and only 300 steps to the 11Y bus, taking commuters to downtown DC.
